# Jarwiz server environment.
# Copy this file to `.env` (same directory) — the server loads it at startup.

# ── ANTHROPIC_API_KEY ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This is the one thing you need for the *full* Jarwiz experience.
#
#   • Set it, and everything runs for real through the Anthropic API — asks,
#     deep web research, Autopilot, the Thinking Machines, clustering, diagrams,
#     link-preview cleanup. Web search uses Anthropic's built-in web_search
#     tool, so this single key covers it too.
#
#   • Leave it unset, and Jarwiz still runs — in demo mode. You get scripted,
#     hand-authored stand-in output so you can explore the canvas with no key.
#     (If you happen to have the Claude Code CLI installed locally, the server
#     uses it as a keyless "sidecar" for real output instead — purely a dev
#     convenience; it is never required.)
#
# The key never leaves the server — the browser only ever sees parsed results.
# Get one at https://console.anthropic.com/
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Port for the HTTP server. The web app's Vite dev proxy expects 3001.
PORT=3001
